    public class FileOps
extends javax.swing.SwingWorker<java.lang.Void,Progress>

      • FileOps

        public FileOps(FileSet files,
               FileOpsMessageHandler handler)
        throws java.lang.IllegalArgumentException
        Constructor that takes a FileSet to conduct operations with and a FileOpsMessageHandler that will take call-backs with Progress updates as the operation progresses.

        Use this constructor when it is desired to receive Progress updates as the copy operation proceeds.

        Parameters:
        files - An existing FileSet that defines parameters of the copy operation (source, destination).
        handler - An instance of FileOpsMessageHandler that will receive progress updates as the operation proceeds.
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - FileSet doesn't exist or is unreadable.
        See Also:
        FileSet, FileOpsMessageHandler

      • cannotWrite

        public static java.lang.Boolean cannotWrite(FileSet fs)
                                     throws java.io.IOException
        Utility function that tests if the destination directory specified in a FileSet can be written to (it must exist and have sufficient permissions to be written to).
        Parameters:
        fs - FileSet to extract the destination directory from.
        Returns:
        Boolean True if the destination is NOT writable
        Throws:
        java.io.IOException - Generally due to a native file system error
